    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Studios in which one or more master textile artist creates works, supervises assistants, and instructs pupils in creating textiles or works made of textiles, which are works that use plant, animal, or synthetic fibers to construct practical or decorative items.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000076089/Black, Fashioning Fabrics: Contemporary Textiles (2006)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000076088/Popovic and Ruck, Textile Artist's Studio Handbook (2012)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Studio's waarin een of meer meester-textielkunstenaars kunstwerken produceren, toezicht houden op assistenten, en leerlingen instrueren in het maken van (producten van) textiel: praktische of decoratieve voorwerpen gemaakt van plantaardige, dierlijke of synthetische vezels.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
